224
00:13:12.562 --> 00:13:16.162
from those footprints to estimate the cancer risk that they would be

225
00:13:16.202 --> 00:13:17.262
associated with.

226
00:13:19.102 --> 00:13:23.062
Now, of course, the changes in patterns of somatic mutation

227
00:13:23.072 --> 00:13:26.842
that are present in normal and cancer cell genomes, these

228
00:13:26.942 --> 00:13:29.902
are footprints of past carcinogen exposures.

229
00:13:30.662 --> 00:13:34.542
They're particularly useful footprints because they're permanent once they've

230
00:13:34.562 --> 00:13:38.462
